FBIS3-16671 "drsov053_v_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-053 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 Lithuania Nationalists Urge Debate WS1703210794 Tallinn BNS in English 1914 GMT 17 Mar 94 WS1703210794 Tallinn BNS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vilnius, Mar 17, BNS -- The political treaty between Lithuania and Poland is not a responsibility of a single party, even the party in power, but a concern of the entire Lithuanian nation, the Board of the Lithuanian Union of Nationalists (LUN) said Thursday [17 March]. In an address to President Algirdas Brazauskas, the LUN suggested to discuss the basic principles of the treaty with all political parties represented in the parliament. The union asks the president to "take the initiative and to achieve a general agreement on this vitally important" problem.
